        "Q4. What is a generator function in python? Why yield keyword is used? Give an example of a generator\n",
        "function."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "aGXt4vITflVs"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "What is a Generator Function in Python?\n",
        "\n",
        "A generator function is a special type of function that returns an iterator and allows you to generate values one at a time instead of storing all of them in memory at once.\n",
        "\n",
        "Generator functions use the yield keyword instead of return.\n",
        "\n",
        "Each time yield is called, the function pauses its state, and resumes from that point when the next value is requested.\n",
        "\n",
        "Why yield is used\n",
        "\n",
        "yield produces a value and pauses the function.\n",
        "\n",
        "This allows lazy evaluation, meaning values are generated on-the-fly, which is memory efficient for large datasets.\n",
        "\n",
        "Example of a Generator Function\n",
        "# Generator function to yield even numbers up to 10\n",
        "def even_numbers():\n",
        "    for num in range(2, 11, 2):\n",
        "        yield num\n",
        "\n",
        "# Using the generator\n",
        "gen = even_numbers()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Printing values one by one\n",
        "for value in gen:\n",
        "    print(value)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "Output:\n",
        "\n",
        "2\n",
        "4\n",
        "6\n",
        "8\n",
        "10\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "✅ Key Points:\n",
        "\n",
        "Generator functions use yield instead of return.\n",
        "\n",
        "They do not store all values in memory, making them efficient.\n",
        "\n",
        "You can iterate over them using for or next().\n",
        "\n",
        "If you want, I can also show an example of a generator for infinite sequences, which is a neat trick in Python. Do you want me to show that?"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EyC4sAHef0pL"
      }
